.TH "hl_get_va_range_type" 9 "hl_get_va_range_type" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hl_get_va_range_type \- get va_range type for the given address and size.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" hl_get_va_range_type
.BI "(struct hl_ctx *ctx "  ","
.BI "u64 address "  ","
.BI "u64 size "  ","
.BI "enum hl_va_range_type *type "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctx" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "address" 12
the start address of the area we want to validate.
.IP "size" 12
the size in bytes of the area we want to validate.
.IP "type" 12
returned va_range type.
.SH "RETURN"
true if the area is inside a valid range, false otherwise.
